SIMPLE: incontinency
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Incontinency
<hw>In*con"ti*nen*cy</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>incontinentia</ets>:
cf. F. <ets>incontinence</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Incapacity to hold; hence, incapacity to hold back
or restrain; the quality or state of being incontinent; lack of
continence; failure to restrain the passions or appetites; indulgence of
lust; lewdness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That Satan tempt you not for your <qex>incontinency</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>1 Cor. vii. 5.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>From the rash hand of bold <qex>incontinence</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>The inability of any of the animal
organs to restrain the natural evacuations, especially urination, or
defecation, so that the discharges are involuntary; <as>as,
<ex>incontinence</ex> of urine</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Incontinent</ent>⟦br⟧
